text: Nassarius lavanonoensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae, the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks. ==Description== The length of the shell varies between 11 mm and 15 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the Indian Ocean off Madagascar. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Nassariidae Category:Gastropods described in 2006
title: Nassarius lavanonoensis
